Don't get me wrong, I like Fallout.  But how can you say the combat is more exciting?  You get to control one guy total.  You get extra people, but you have almost no control over them.  (All you can do is select their weapon, armor, and fighting style.."Flee at 5 hp")<br>
<br>
<br>
Atleast in BG you get control over 6 people, requiring much more strategy than Fallout does.<br>
<br>
The maximum amount of strategy in Fallout's fights are "Should I use burst or aim shot?"<br>
<br>
<br>
Character depth in Fallout?  Explain.  BG isn't much better, but atleast there is a story behind it.  In Fallout, all you get is "The choosen one" and *very* minor factions.  (Mostly controled by Karma which is more of a global faction.)  They also have generally pointless titles (Most are, anyways.. Some play a part).  I ran around as a grave digger and a child killer for the entire game and never experience any problems. Am I missing something?  Maybe the point system, which lets you choose between fighting or sneaking, but <b>I <u>personally</u></b> don't like that type of system.  There's always the kick ass template that is uberer than all of the others, and then the weaker ones.  (I'm not saying that there's only one way to have a good character, I'm just saying it's not as deep as it appears)<br>
<br>
I'm not bashing Fallout, I love it.  I was a major addict at one time.  I just never saw the stuff you mentioned.  But like I said, it's not much better in BG..but the story does a lot for it.  Just being "The choosen one" is kinda dull..<br>
